{"id":"2007.06592","submitter":"Lukas Semmelrock","authors":"Josef Pradler and Lukas Semmelrock","title":"Exact Theory of Non-relativistic Quadrupole Bremsstrahlung","comments":"23 pages, 6 figures, ApJ style; minor typos corrected; journal\n  version","journal-ref":null,"doi":"10.3847/1538-4357/abc9c5","report-no":null,"categories":"hep-ph","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  The quantum mechanical treatment of quadrupole radiation due to\nbremsstrahlung exact to all orders in the Coulomb interaction of two\nnon-relativistically colliding charged spin-0 and unpolarized spin-1/2\nparticles is presented. We calculate the elements of the quadrupole tensor, and\npresent analytical solutions for the double differential photon emission cross\nsection of identical and non-identical particles. Contact is made to Born-level\nand quasi-classical results in the respective kinematic limits and effective\nenergy loss rates are obtained. A generally valid formula for soft-photon\nemission is established and an approximate formula across the entire kinematic\nregime is constructed. The results apply to bremsstrahlung emission in the\nscattering of pairs of electrons and are hence relevant in the study of\nastrophysical phenomena. A definition of a Gaunt factor is proposed which\nshould facilitate broad applicability of the results.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 13 Jul 2020 18:00:28 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 30 Nov 2020 11:26:09 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 21 Dec 2021 12:52:44 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-12-22"}
