mics resulting from the reduced phase\nspace quantization including the resolution of the big bang singularity via a\nquantum bounce, and effects of the different reference fields on e-foldings in\nboth the pre-inflationary and the slow-roll inflationary phases. We find that\ndifferent clocks, even when starting with a small but same energy density, can\nleave tiny but different imprints on the inflationary dynamics. (abridged)\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 13 Jul 2020 18:01:08 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 7 Dec 2020 22:22:53 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-01-04"}
