{"id":"2007.07209","submitter":"Shibashis Guha","authors":"Mrudula Balachander, Shibashis Guha, Jean-Fran\\c{c}ois Raskin","title":"Fragility and Robustness in Mean-Payoff Adversarial Stackelberg Games","comments":"Full version of paper accepted in CONCUR 2021","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.OC cs.GT math.CO","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  Two-player mean-payoff Stackelberg games are nonzero-sum infinite duration\ngames played on a bi-weighted graph by Leader (Player 0) and Follower (Player\n1). Such games are played sequentially: first, Leader announces her strategy,\nsecond, Follower chooses his best-response. If we cannot impose which\nbest-response is chosen by Follower, we say that Follower, though strategic, is\nadversarial towards Leader. The maximal value that Leader can get in this\nnonzero-sum game is called the adversarial Stackelberg value (ASV) of the game.\n  We study the robustness of strategies for Leader in these games against two\ntypes of deviations: (i) Modeling imprecision - the weights on the edges of the\ngame arena may not be exactly correct, they may be delta-away from the right\none. (ii) Sub-optimal response - Follower may play epsilon-optimal\nbest-responses instead of perfect best-responses. First, we show that if the\ngame is zero-sum then robustness is guaranteed while in the nonzero-sum case,\noptimal strategies for ASV are fragile. Second, we provide a solution concept\nto obtain strategies for Leader that are robust to both modeling imprecision,\nand as well as to the epsilon-optimal responses of Follower, and study several\nproperties and algorithmic problems related to this solution concept.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 13 Jul 2020 17:44:46 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 16 Jul 2020 16:48:45 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 5 Nov 2020 15:39:50 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Sun, 7 Feb 2021 10:32:51 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Mon, 2 Aug 2021 19:39:27 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-08-04"}
